lation of antidepressants, Ecks theorizes value as a process of biocommensuration. Biocommensurations—transactions that aim or claim to make life better—are those forms of social, medical, and corporate actions that allow value to be measured, exchanged, substituted, and redistributed. Ecks’s theory expands value beyond both a Marxist labor theory of value and a free market subjective theory, thereby offering new insights into how the value of lives and things become entangled under neoliberal capitalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aAntidepressantsxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aAntidepressantszIndia. 0aDepressed personszIndia. 0aDepression, MentalxTreatmentzIndia. 0aMental healthxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aPharmaceutical industryxEconomic aspectszIndia. 0aPharmaceutical industryxMoral and ethical aspectszIndia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478022282423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478022282/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles